==English==

===Etymology===
{{F.}} balustre, It. balaustro, fr. L. balaustium the flower of the wild pomegranate, fr. Gr. balay`stion; -- so named from the similarity of form.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈbæl.ʌ.str/

===Noun===
'''baluster'''
# A short column used in a group to support a rail, as commonly found on the side of a stairway.

